inlineContent.text: The clinical record stores information about a single condition, procedure, or result. While the record’s properties expose some high-level information, the
property contains the underlying data from the user’s healthcare institution.
Note that the record inherits the
properties. However, the system does not populate these properties with information from the FHIR data; instead, the
reflect the time and date when the system downloaded the FHIR data to the device.
